SIMPLE: fingerboard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fingerboard
<hw>fingerboard</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a guidepost
resembling a hand with a pointing index finger.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fingerpost.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a bank of keys on a musical instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> piano keyboard, clavier.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a narrow strip of wood on the neck of some stringed
instruments (violin or cello or guitar etc) where the strings are held
against the wood with the fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fingerbreadth</ent>⟦br⟧
